    "attributes": {
        "action": "Establish a Public Inquiry into the Chaotic Return to University in 2020",
        "additional_details": "Several factors contributed to the chaotic start of university term, most obviously the Covid-19 virus.\r\n \r\nWe must, however, understand the other factors to prevent such damage in future, including but not limited to:\r\n\r\n- Need for universities to compete for student fees\r\n- Underfunding of research, which led to overreliance on overseas student fee income\r\n- Role of private accommodation providers\r\n- Structure of university governance\r\n- Lack of coordination between sector-wide bodies and government",
        "background": "A public inquiry is needed to investigate why the start of academic term 2020/21 resulted in: students being prevented from leaving accommodation, overworked academic staff, concerns about university finances, all without clear steer or support from Government.",
